      • getAssociatedPolicyInternal

        public Policy getAssociatedPolicyInternal()
        Retrieves this Vehicle's associated policy, if possible. This method assumes that the Vehicle is tied to the policy either via an Incident (i.e., Policy <- Claim -> VehicleIncident -> Vehicle) or via a VehicleRU (i.e., Policy <- VehicleRU -> Vehicle) as is always true in the uncustomized datamodel. If that is not the case, then this method will return NULL.
        Returns:
        The Policy entity associated with this Vehicle entity, if that association is as expected from the uncustomized datamodel. If not, then NULL will be returned.

      • validateLienholders

        public java.lang.String validateLienholders()
        Checks that there are no duplicate lienholders in the getLienholders() array. If there are any duplicate lienholders returns an error describing the duplication. This method is suitable for use as a "validationExpression" in a PCF file
        Returns:
        null if there are no duplicate lienholders, otherwise a localized string describing the duplication
